 for bestpractices and # Inquiry Form (Auth-Gated)

## Overview
Build an authenticated, multi-field stay inquiry form that gates access behind user authentication. This page collects high-quality guest inquiries—including destination, arrival/departure dates, guest count, room/suite preferences, budget hints, and special requests—while supporting draft saving, optional attachments, and inline validation. The flow should integrate with an administrative/host-facing inquiry management system where staff can view, update statuses, add internal notes, export data, and reconcile payments manually. The implementation must strictly guard against null/undefined values when dealing with arrays and API results, and adhere to the runtime safety guidelines provided.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Inquiry Form (Auth-Gated) page is a gated, premium, editorial-style form used by authenticated guests to submit stay inquiries. It pre-fills destination data from the selected listing, captures extended stay details, accommodates flexibility (flexible dates), and allows optional attachments to contextualize the inquiry.

Goals:
- Ensure authenticated guests can submit comprehensive inquiries with high-quality data.
- Provide a user-friendly, resilient UI with inline validation, draft autosave, and clear submission states.
- Seamlessly connect to the internal admin/host management workflow, where staff can view, update, attach notes, and export inquiries.
- Maintain data safety and integrity with robust client-side validation and secure data handling (no API integration in this prompt; placeholders noted).

Connected features:
- Inquiry Submission & Management: Guest submission flow, admin/host management, lifecycle tracking (New, Contacted, Deposit Paid, Confirmed, etc.), attachments, and status notes.
- Draft autosave and persistence per user session.
- Optional manual payment trigger workflow (Stripe Connect is referenced in project scope but integration is outside this prompt; include placeholders for status transitions and payment flagging).

UI elements and visual guidance:
- Auth Gate: When unauthenticated, present a modal or redirect to login/signup with a concise privacy note and seamless return flow.
- Destination Details: Destination name, city, region, and a short description (pre-filled from the selected listing); show a hero image or thumbnail and a gallery if available.
- Form Fields:
  - Destination (read-only, pre-filled)
  - Arrival Date (date picker)
  - Departure Date (date picker)
  - Flexible Dates toggle (checkbox)
  - Number of Guests (numeric selector)
  - Room/Suite Preferences (multi-select or dropdown: Studio, 1BR, 2BR, etc.; special requests recommended as notes)
  - Budget Hint (optional)
  - Special Requests/Notes (multiline text area)
  - Attachments (optional): multiple file upload with size/type validation (e.g., PDF, DOCX, images)
  - Contact Preferences: Email, SMS, or Phone (opt-in)
- Save as Draft: Auto-save drafts at a reasonable interval (e.g., every 60 seconds) or on field blur.
- Validation & Inline Errors: Real-time validation with inline hints; show summary of errors at the top if any.
- Submission State: Button shows loading state on submit; success state with confirmation number and next steps (e.g., “We’ll be in touch”).
- Privacy Notice: Short, clear copy about data handling and consent.
- Confirmation: Submission confirmation view with a reference ID, and an option to navigate to the admin dashboard or back to destination page.
- Accessibility: All controls labeled, keyboard accessible, and proper aria attributes; high-contrast focus outlines in the design system.

UI styling guidance:
- Follow the Visual Style section (colors, typography, spacing, and components) to render a premium, editorial experience consistent with Roam Resort branding.
- Cards for destination details with soft shadows, rounded corners, and hover states.
- Primary CTAs use bronze-gold (#A97C50); secondary actions use beige with bronze outlines.
- Typography: Headings in Playfair Display (or similar); body text in Inter/Lato with ample line-height for readability.
- Layout: Centered hero intro for landing, left-aligned content for the form in a responsive grid, with generous vertical spacing (40–80px between sections).

API integrations:
- This prompt does not wire API endpoints; instead, it defines required data shapes, validation rules, and UI interactions. Placeholders for API calls should be present with proper error handling and null-safety, ready for integration with:
  - Inquiries API (create, update draft, fetch listing data)
  - Attachments API (upload, link to inquiry)
  - Admin export API (CSV)
  - Payment state hooks (placeholder)

Accessibility and testing considerations:
- All fields labeled, with aria-invalid and aria-live regions for error messages.
- Keyboard shortcuts for primary actions (Submit: Enter when focused on the form, Draft: accessible via auto-save indicator).
- Unit tests should cover: form validation rules, draft autosave behavior, guard against null/undefined arrays, and correct handling of optional attachments.

## Components to Build
- AuthGateModal
  - Props: isOpen, onClose, redirectTo, user
  - Behavior: prompts login/signup; returns to the current page after authentication
- DestinationHeaderCard
  - Props: destination, image, description
  - Read-only display of destination data
- InquiryForm
  - Props: destinationId, destinationName, existingDraft (optional)
  - State: dates, guests, roomPrefs, flexibleDates, budget, notes, attachments, contactPrefs, draftId
  - Methods: handleChange, validate, submitInquiry, saveDraft, addAttachment, removeAttachment
- AttachmentUploader
  - Props: onFilesChange, maxSize, allowedTypes
  - State: files
  - Behavior: client-side validation, previews for images, convert non-image types to icons
- InquiryStatusPanel (admin)
  - Props: inquiry
  - Behavior: status dropdown, add internal notes, export action trigger
- AdminInquiryList
  - Props: inquiries, onSelect
  - Behavior: filter by status, search, sort
- DraftAutoSaver
  - Hook: useEffect-based autosave, debounced to prevent excessive writes
- ValidationUtils
  - Helpers: isValidDateRange(start, end), isPastDate(date), isPositiveInt(n), isArrayGuard(value)
- API Mocks / Interfaces (for development)
  - Types: Destination, Inquiry, Attachment, User
  - Functions: fetchDestination(destId), saveInquiry(inquiry), updateInquiry(inquiry), uploadAttachment(file)

All components must guard against null/undefined values before calling array methods:
- Always use (data ?? []) or Array.isArray(data) checks before .map, .filter, .reduce, etc.
- Initialize state with proper defaults: useState<Inquiry[]>([]) where arrays are expected.
- Validate API responses safely: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
- Access nested fields safely: obj?.field?.subfield
- Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Pages/Routes:
  - /inquiry/[destinationId] or /inquiry (depending on routing)
  - Protected route wrapper that redirects to login if not authenticated
- UI Components:
  - Reusable form controls following design system (input, textarea, select, date picker, toggle, checkbox)
  - Attachment uploader with drag-and-drop support and progress indicators
  - Inline validation messages and a top-level error summary
- State Management:
  - Use React useState/useEffect or your preferred state library to manage form state
  - Persist drafts to localStorage or user-scoped API draft save (respect privacy)
- Autosave:
  - Implement DraftAutoSaver with a debounce (e.g., 1 minute) to persist draft state
- Accessibility:
  - All interactive elements have aria-labels; meaningful focus order; screen-reader friendly
- Security:
  - Ensure client-side checks enforce authentication before submission; do not rely on UI alone

### Backend
- APIs (placeholders for now, with data contracts):
  - POST /inquiries (create or update draft if id exists)
  - GET /destinations/{id} (fetch destination data)
  - POST /inquiries/{id}/attachments (upload)
  - GET /inquiries?destinationId=... (admin listing, guarded)
  - PATCH /inquiries/{id} (update status, notes, contact prefs)
  - POST /inquiries/export (generate CSV)
- Database Tables (design surface):
  - inquiries: id, destination_id, user_id, arrival_date, departure_date, flexible_dates, guests, room_prefs, budget_hint, notes, attachments (array of file refs), contact_preferences, status, created_at, updated_at
  - attachments: id, inquiry_id, file_url, mime_type, name, size, uploaded_at
  - users: id, email, name, role (guest/host/admin)
- Validation:
  - Ensure required fields on create: destination_id, arrival_date, departure_date, guests, room_prefs
  - Date range validation on backend; dates must be in future or current date
  - Attachment size/type validation

### Integration
- Data Flow:
  - On page load, fetch destination data; initialize form with destination details
  - User fills form; drafts autosave to storage
  - On submit, create or update inquiry record; upload attachments if any
  - Admin panel consumes inquiries API; status transitions and notes stored in same record
- Error Handling:
  - Graceful error messages; retry logic for network failures; security-conscious messages

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on the Destination Inquiry page (Auth-Gated)
2. If not authenticated, AuthGateModal prompts login/signup
3. After authentication, DestinationHeaderCard is visible with destination details
4. User completes InquiryForm with fields: dates, guests, room preferences, notes, and optional attachments
5. Auto-save runs in the background; draft persists locally or in API draft store
6. User reviews inline validations; corrects any issues
7. User clicks Submit; form shows loading state
8. On success, user sees confirmation screen with reference ID and suggested next steps
9. If guest needs to edit, they can reopen the draft and update
10. Admins/Hosts access AdminInquiryList to view and manage inquiries, update statuses, add internal notes, and export CSV

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: [Schema details]
- Destination
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - city: string
  - country: string
  - description: string
  - imageUrl: string
- Inquiry
  - id: string
  - destination_id: string
  - user_id: string
  - arrival_date: string (ISO)
  - departure_date: string (ISO)
  - flexible_dates: boolean
  - guests: number
  - room_prefs: string[]
  - budget_hint?: string
  - notes: string
  - attachments: Attachment[]
  - contact_preferences: { email?: string; sms?: string; phone?: string }
  - status: string (New, Contacted, Deposit Paid, Confirmed, etc.)
  - created_at: string
  - updated_at: string
- Attachment
  - id: string
  - inquiry_id: string
  - file_url: string
  - mime_type: string
  - name: string
  - size: number
  - uploaded_at: string

API Endpoints: [Routes and methods]
- GET /destinations/{id}
- POST /inquiries
  - Body: { destination_id, user_id, arrival_date, departure_date, flexible_dates, guests, room_prefs, budget_hint, notes, contact_preferences }
- PATCH /inquiries/{id}
  - Body: { status, notes, contact_preferences, ... }
- POST /inquiries/{id}/attachments
  - FormData: { file }
- GET /inquiries?destination_id=... (admin)
- POST /inquiries/export
  - Body: { filter: { status, dateRange, destination_id } }

Security: [Authentication, authorization requirements]
- Guest: authenticated users can create/update their own inquiries
- Host/Admin: authenticated users with roles 'host' or 'admin' can read all inquiries, update status, add internal notes, and export
- Ensure all endpoints enforce proper role checks server-side
- Data minimization: only necessary fields exposed to guests

Validation: [Input validation rules]
- arrival_date, departure_date: required; departure after arrival
- guests: required; > 0
